Department of School Education and CRODA

Date: 19th March, 2025
Reference: -

1) Director of Education, Directorate of Education (Planning), Pune. 12.09.2024 and d. Letter dated 11.03.2025 2) Department of Finance, Government Circular No. Meaning 2024 / Q. No.80 / Mean-3, D. 25.07.2024 and D. 12.02.2025
The Proposal: -

The Maha DBT portal has been developed by the Maharashtra Information Technology Corporation to implement the Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT) scheme of the Government of Maharashtra. The following two schemes under the Department of School Education and CRODA are implemented through the DBT portal from the year 2018-2019.
a) Open Quality Scholarships at Junior College level b) Quality Scholarships for Economically Backward Students

Payments of fees charged in respect of services rendered for implementation of both the above mentioned schemes at the level of Director of Education, Directorate of Education (Planning), Pune have been submitted to the Government by Maharashtra Information CIA Corporation from time to time, these payments have been certified by Director of Education (Planning), Pune. In respect of the said schemes, the Technical Assistants appointed by the DBT Portal for online work will be paid a total of Rs. 14,64,060 - Maharashtra Information Technology Corporation Ltd. The issue of administrative and financial approval of their payment was under the consideration of the government.
The Government's Decisions:

Maharashtra Information Technology Corporation Limited (MIDCL) has invited applications from eligible candidates to apply for open quality scholarships at junior college level and quality scholarships for economically backward students on the DBT portal for technical assistants appointed for online processing for the period January, 2019 to December, 2024.
